rules: Rule1: If the project has an approved blueprint, then the project is successful.
Rule2: Either the project has an approved blueprint or the project has secured funding.
Rule3: Provided that materials are delivered on schedule, the project is successful.
Rule4: Whenever the concrete supplier is reliable, materials are delivered on schedule.
Rule5: Under the condition that the steel supplier is reliable, materials are delivered on schedule.
Rule6: If foundation work has started, then either the concrete supplier is reliable or the steel supplier is reliable.
Rule7: In the event that foundation work is delayed, either the concrete supplier is reliable or the steel supplier is reliable.
Rule8: Given that excavation is complete, foundation work has started or foundation work is delayed.
Rule9: Excavation is complete or excavation is not complete.
Rule10: Either the structural design is flawed or, if excavation is not complete, then foundation work has started or foundation work is delayed.
Rule11: Whenever cost controls are implemented, expenses are tracked daily.
Rule12: Given that variance is analyzed weekly, the budget is not exceeded.
Rule13: Should quality standards be met, then if expenses are tracked daily, variance is analyzed weekly.
Rule14: Whenever contractor performance is satisfactory, if a project milestone is missed, then a project milestone is achieved.
Rule15: Either contractor performance is satisfactory or contractor performance is poor.
Rule16: If contractor performance is poor, then penalties are applied.
Rule17: Under the condition that penalties are applied, then if a project milestone is missed, a project milestone is achieved.
Rule18: Given that weather conditions are favorable, materials storage is not inadequate.
Rule19: Should weather conditions be monitored, materials storage is not inadequate.
Rule20: If safety protocols are enforced, then safety training is conducted.
Rule21: Should PPE usage be verified, then either weather conditions are favorable or weather conditions are monitored.
Rule22: Whenever safety inspections are regular, PPE usage is verified.
Rule23: If incident reports are filed, then safety inspections are regular.
Rule24: Either a compliance certificate is issued or, if safety training is conducted, then incident reports are filed.
Rule25: Provided that the foundation inspection passed, foundation work has started.
Rule26: Under the condition that site preparation is incomplete, the permit is not denied.
Rule27: Site preparation is incomplete or site preparation is ready.
Rule28: Given that the foundation inspection is pending, foundation work is delayed.
Rule29: Either structural integrity is compromised or the foundation inspection passed or the foundation inspection is pending.
Rule30: Should materials testing be completed, the quality of materials is not substandard.
Rule31: Whenever an alternative supplier is identified, materials rejection is not necessary.
Rule32: Either the supplier contract is terminated or an alternative supplier is identified.
Rule33: A budget review is scheduled or a budget review is an emergency.
Rule34: Under the condition that a budget review is an emergency, then either a cost overrun is prevented or, if cost controls are implemented, the budget is not exceeded.
Rule35: Should corrective actions be implemented, then either a cost overrun is prevented or, if cost controls are implemented, the budget is not exceeded.
Rule36: Whenever the financial audit is clean, then if a budget review is scheduled, corrective actions are implemented.
Rule37: In the event that issues are found in the financial audit, then if a budget review is scheduled, corrective actions are implemented.
Rule38: Under the condition that client approval is received, the project delay is not significant.
Rule39: Client approval is received or client approval is pending.
Rule40: Given that client approval is pending, the project delay is not significant.
Rule41: Should equipment be insufficient, then if site preparation is ready, the permit is not denied.
Rule42: Equipment is insufficient or equipment is adequate.
Rule43: Either the safety audit failed or, if equipment is adequate, then if site preparation is ready, the permit is not denied.
Rule44: Provided that the safety audit passed, the safety audit did not fail.
Rule45: If it is not true that if the project has secured funding then the project is successful, then the permit is denied.
Rule46: Should it not be the case that if a project phase is completed then either the financial audit is clean or issues are found, then the project delay is significant.
Rule47: Provided that it is not the case that if it is not true that foundation work has started or foundation work is delayed then foundation work is halted, then a project milestone is missed.
Rule48: Under the condition that it is not the case that if the project is not successful then adjusting the timeline is necessary, then the budget is exceeded.
Rule49: Given that it is not the case that if the project is not successful then adjusting the timeline is necessary, then cost controls are implemented.
Rule50: If materials are not delivered on schedule, then materials storage is inadequate.
Rule51: Whenever materials are not delivered on schedule, the quality of materials is substandard.
Rule52: Provided that materials testing is not completed, materials rejection is necessary.
facts: Fact3: A project phase is completed.
Fact5: It is not the case that the structural design is flawed.
Fact6: Adjusting the timeline is not necessary.
Fact7: Foundation work is not halted.
Fact8: A project milestone is not achieved.
Fact9: A compliance certificate is not issued.
Fact10: Structural integrity is not compromised.
Fact11: The supplier contract is not terminated.
Fact12: A cost overrun is not prevented.
